when we run ls -l one of the result is

-r--rw-rw-. 1 calvin calvin 22 Feb 25 13:02 abc1

here calvin is the owner of the file, and we see another calvin next to calvin, so the secon calvin is 
the group. only root can change the ownerships

we use "chown" for owner
"chown ownerName fileName"

if i remove calvin as owner and make it root, then i can lose some permission, so i need to be root and do it.

we use "chgrp" for the group
